{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":17384,"name":"","username":"vivienneanthony","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/vivienneanthony/{size}/942_2.png","created_at":"2017-04-25T20:28:19.467Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI ran into a problem previously. There was a nice tweak to work. I was getting material artifacting if near clip was zero or to low. I left a issue of it at \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/issues/1920\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/issues/1920\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"http://imgur.com/a/yyP7q\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://imgur.com/a/yyP7q\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen I set the near clip of the camera to 1.0f it helped solve the problem. Ideally I would like to move the camera for example 1km from a object and still have it show visibly okay.  At minimum a near clip of 0.1f or lower, to 8192km far clip. It might be a little extreme.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdeally I would like to model objects full scale as 1.0 equal to 1 meter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny thoughts or help appreciated. As I‚Äôm not sure what internal Urho3D updates is needed to make that possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVivienne\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-04-25T20:28:19.467Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":126,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":641.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3049,"topic_slug":"improving-near-and-far-clipping","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://imgur.com/a/yyP7q","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Imgur: The most awesome images on the Internet","clicks":28},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/issues/1920","internal":false,"reflec